article.linkText: McFarlane, Caldwell lead SE Louisiana over Incarnate Word 76-64
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- — Roger McFarlane and Nick Caldwell scored 18 points apiece to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 76-64 victory over Incarnate Word on Monday night. McFarlane added seven rebounds for the Lions (10-13, 5-5 Southland Conference). Caldwell sank 8 of 10 shots and grabbed eight boards. Alec Woodard hit three 3-pointers and scored 16. Sky Wicks finished with 15 points and two blocks for the Cardinals (7-15, 2-7). Josiah Hammons added 14 points. Alex Anderson totaled 13 points and seven assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
